		<p>we assume that by 40 weeks you should deliver. But that's not true some pregnancies are stretched up till 41 weeks or 41 completed weeks. you are not post term until you finish your 42nd week. By this time your doctor has probably discuss labour induction with you but that doesn't mean that you won't still go into labour on your own some babies just need to take their own time.</p>
