		<p><b>Tips </b></p>
		<p><b>Over due or stressed?</b></p>
		<p>even if you have past 40 weeks it doesn't mean that you are overdue, in fact an estimated 70% of post pregnancies are not actually late at all but a misscalculation of the date of conception.</p>
		<p><b>you might loss weight: </b>your weighing scale instead of going up may stand still or go down . so what triggers this typical late pregnancy weight Trend is tactually your body was busily accumulating  fluid that now it wont need once the baby making factory is shut down and that fluid includes a drop in amniotic fluid as well as increase in more pee.</p>
		<p>you may also be sweating more the more you sweat, the more weight you lose.</p>
		<p><b>what expect during labour?</b></p>
		<p>if you are having an unmedicated birth your contractions will soon become too strong for you to talk through them this is when you will start your breathing exercise you might be offered a light snack or clear a beverages to keep you hydrated or you might get an i v to maintain fluids if you want between contractions walk around a bit if you can or change positions make sure you continue to urinate regularly staff at the hospital will be on hand to take your blood precious time your contractions and monitor the baby's position and progress of labour either via a Doppler or electronic fetal monitoring if you do opt for an epidural or if it's hospitals policy you will be hooked up to an IV to maintain your fluids and you'll probably also be hooked up to a continuous fetal monitor unless you have a walking epidural you may not be able to move your legs very much but do try to change positions if you can.</p>
		<p><b>eat protein : </b>you should go light on diet when you are approaching your labour but cutting down on protein  is something not advisable. you should eat protein because it is a must  for your mind and for your baby's body building blocks so keep protein by your side.</p>
		<p>try relaxation exercise</p>
		<p>try the following relaxation exercises </p>
		<p>tense your facial muscles for 5 seconds then relax then do the same with your neck muscles, then your shoulders working your way down your body and remember to breathe slowly. Need more help relaxing listen to your favourite soothing tunes, no heavy metal please and start the breathing. A you can listen any meditative music as well.</p>
		<p><b>nesting instincts : </b>On the other hand you may notice a sudden burst of energy now and then. If you felt in immediate urge, to say, organize the nursery closet , that's the nesting Instincts, kicking into high gear which is nature's way of helping you to prepare for your impending arrival.</p>
